  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 12:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G/Price Divergence: Fear at 8, BTC Up 2.8%\n\n**Task:** Analyze why 12h produced zero trades. Understand F&G/price relationship.\n\n**Finding:**\n- **12h: zero trades.** 38 minutes of 100% bullish bias. Not a single negative reading. PM YES at 0.465 (market strongly pricing UP).\n- **BTC rallied $66,011 \u2192 $67,881 (+2.8%) while F&G = 8 (Extreme Fear)**\n- This is a classic \"wall of worry\" climb \u2014 maximum bearish sentiment, bullish price\n\n**Why our strategy struggles in this regime:**\n1. Our strategy is contrarian to ORDER FLOW (fading bearish bias)\n2. In an uptrend, order flow is persistently bullish \u2192 no bearish signals to fade\n3. When pullbacks do occur, they're shallow ($17 range) \u2192 noise, not signal\n4. The market is ALREADY contrarian to sentiment (price up despite fear) \u2014 there's no additional contrarian edge\n\n**Trade frequency analysis:**\n- Pre-V3 (Mar 20-26): 20.5 trades/day\n- Post-V3 (Mar 27-30): 3.25 trades/day\n- Today: 2 real signals in 1.5 active hours (double-fire bug inflated to 5 executions)\n\n**BTC context:**\n- Dropped $72K\u2192$65K (Mar 25-29), now bouncing\n- Current $67,857 = 41% of weekly range (mid-range, not overbought)\n- Key level: $68,042 (today's high) \u2014 break above = continuation, fail = pullback\n- 50% Fibonacci retrace of drop = $68,500\n\n**Decision:** No changes. Low trade days are expected in strong trends. Our edge is in RANGE-bound markets with oscillating bias. Today is trending bullish \u2014 patience is correct. The 19h/20h session may see different dynamics as US traders enter.\n\n## 2026-03-30 12:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] 11h Post-Mortem: Pullback Trading in a Rally\n\n**Task:** Full analysis of V4.1's first active hour. Understand signal-to-trade ratio and loss patterns.\n\n**Finding:**\n- **204 rejections, 5 trades** (2.4% signal-to-trade ratio)\n- **56% YES_ONLY_FILTER** \u2014 market was predominantly bullish (BTC rallied $422)\n- WR: 2W/2L = 50% (1 trade unconfirmed) \u2014 below 88% historical\n- Only 18% of bias readings were YES-qualifying (< -25)\n\n**Bias oscillation pattern:**\n| Window | Avg Bias | YES Signals | Trades | Result |\n|--------|----------|-------------|--------|--------|\n| 11:00-11:14 | +16.9 | 0 | 0 | \u2014 |\n| 11:15-11:24 | **-7.0** | 4 | 2 | \u274c\u274c |\n| 11:25-11:34 | +45.6 | 0 | 0 | \u2014 |\n| 11:35-11:44 | **-25.2** | 13 | 3 | \u2705\u2705(\u2705) |\n| 11:45-11:59 | +24.2 | 6 | 0 | \u2014 |\n\n**Key insight:** In a trending market, our contrarian strategy fires on pullbacks. The deeper the pullback, the more reliable the signal:\n- 11:15 pullback: BTC -$17 \u2192 noise \u2192 LOSS\n- 11:35 pullback: BTC -$47 \u2192 genuine dip \u2192 WIN\n\n**V5 idea: BTC move minimum filter.** If the current 5-min candle range is < $40 at entry time, the pullback may be noise. Would have filtered both losses today (range $17) while keeping all wins (range $45+). Need 20+ trades to validate.\n\n**Decision:** Collect data. Current filters are working (the 50% WR is just 4 trades \u2014 not statistically significant). The double-trade bug inflated both wins and losses. Clean data",
